When *Show Link Icons* is enabled in Confluence, the icon shown on links to user profiles differs based on whether the user has a personal space or not.  If they do not have a personal space, the image shown is /images/icons/user_12.gif.  If they do have a personal space, the image shown is /images/icons/personal_space_12.jpg.  The icon *personal_space_12.jpg* is not a transparent image.

To reproduce this I identified one user which has a personal space and one which does not.  For this example, the former is "justin" and the latter is "testuser".  I then made a child page in our site's Demonstration Space with the following markup:

{code}
{panel:title=testing some transparency|borderStyle=dashed|borderColor=blue|titleBGColor=#00a400|titleColor=white|bgColor=#72bc72}
[~justin]
[~testuser]
text
{panel}
{code}

The results are:
!Screen Shot 2011-07-17 at 19.09.55 PM.JPEG!

I recommend that this image be replaced with a transparent equivalent.

