The modal frame for IE7 and Confluence 3.5.x for "Link to this Page" is rendered incorrectly.

This has been confirmed by Support (Anna and Vincent).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-22778].
  {panel}

The addMembership method returns the InsufficientPrivilegeException when the group does not exist, even when the user has sufficient permissions to add a user to a group. Additionally, if the "confluence-users" group does not exist or the "users" group in Confluence only OnDemand, this error can occur when trying to create a new user in Confluence.

The exception thrown suggests a permissions problem:
{code}
com.atlassian.confluence.core.InsufficientPrivilegeException: User [user.name] does not have the required privileges.
    at com.atlassian.confluence.user.DefaultUserAccessor.addMembership(DefaultUserAccessor.java:118)
{code}

However this exception is wrong/misleading, and does not reflect the true cause of failure, which is that the group does not exist.

On a side note, we have KB article on this, but I didn't find a bug filed for it:
http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CONFKB/Unable+to+Create+New+User+Due+to+InsufficientPrivilegeException

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-22769].
  {panel}

Many times people in work groups upload attachments to pages - and there needs to be discussion about the attachment - but ideally each could be on its own page. 
Currently, each attachment has a "View" link - which takes you to a page where you can view the attachment, but you cannot add a comment.

It would be great if when viewing the attachment, it could act somewhat like a confluence page, and have the ability to add comments at the bottom, to facilitate discussion of attachments, especially for PDFs, but really for any kind of attachments.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-22764].
  {panel}

The DefaultI18N bean, seems to be trying to escape { and } to avoid confusing the message formatter. However there seems to be a bug with it. The current code is 
{code}
 // CONF-15946 - Escape '{' and '}' characters on keys if no args present and not already escaped.
        if(result.indexOf("'{") == -1 && result.indexOf("'}") == -1) {
            if(args == null || args.length == 0) {
                result = result.replaceAll("\\{", "'{").replaceAll("\\}", "'}");
            }
        }
{code}
As is visible, it checks if "{" and "}" is present, and if they are *NOT* present it tries to escape them.

